node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Lessons I learned from the book "Rich Dad, Poor Dad." o @er ntrepreneursquote treprer (Ath)'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1) Put your money to work. You cannot get rich with your money in a savings account. You have to invest in appreciating assets.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2) Gain financial knowledge. Learn about investing, business, markets, accounting, sales, etc. It will help you make overall better financial decisions.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3) It isn't about how much you make. How much money you make is important, out what's even more important is how much you KEEP'.
Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4) Acquire assets. Rich people acquires assets while poor accumulates liabilities.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5) You aren't born to to work for others. Most people consider a 9-5 job as something they've supposed to be dealing with for the rest of their lives. Completely forgetting the life possible beyong that.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6) Winning means not being afraid to lose. Never be afraid to take calculated risks. Those who play it safe never make big fortunes.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7) Pay yourself first. Every month, first invest in your income-generating assets. The rest of expenses should be next to it.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Quick recap: Put your money to work 2. Gain financial knowledge 3. It isn't about how much you make 4. Acquire assets 5. You aren't born to work for others 6. Winning means not being afraid to lose 7. Pay yourself first'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou Biggest financial mistakes early in my journey: (a thread)'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #1- Choosing the Wrong Business Model I put over 200k in a restaurant business that didn't produce profits until it burned down-| couldn't even afford insurance for it and so I lost everything in that fire I put 5k in Amazon and made millions with it- huge difference'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Basha J Katou @basharjkatou #2- 2- Being Cheap I didn't want to spend money, so I paid my employees the minimum Because of that they were not loyal to me and couldn't care less when I lost everything. They were even threatening me to beat me up if I didn't pay them the salary they still were owerd right after everything burned down'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Basha J Katou @basharjkatou #3- Being Stubborn When When I finally was ready to start a new business, I was too proud and stubborn to realize sucked as a business owner. I refused to pay a coach, mentor or consultant for advice and lost several thousands of dollars to that ignorance'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #4- Having a Scarcity Mindset I was taught that everyone is out to get me and I need to protect my money. I thought everyone is trying to scam me and that fear stopped me from growing as a person. If everyone is out to get me, who could I ask for help, who could I hire, how would I charge customers a fair price?'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou #5- Flexing As soon as I made my first big money, bought a Bentley Luckily, soon realized flexing isn't who I am and sold it after a few months. Still was a huge waste of money'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Basha J Katou @basharjkatou #6- Thinking Having the Cheapest Prices is Good If your only selling point is being cheap, anyone can put you out of business by being cheaper. Selling cheap means you can't deliver quality and only quality creates a lasting business'.

Photo shared by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bashar J Katou @basharjkatou If you want to start your business, don't make the mistakes I made Do it right from the get-go. If you want to build a business your customers will love to pay you for, follow my page for more tips! (@basharjkatou)'.
Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Some people are investments, some people are bills Know the difference.'.
